Subject: Re: [T2] help re-installing cylinders/heads on a two litre

At 01:26 PM 4/9/2003, Paul Archibald wrote:
>Now gettng ready to reinstall, I slipped off the cylinders
>and honed them, than attempted to pull out the piston pins
>to remove the pistons to put the new rings in....here's te
>trouble...fought to get teh circlip out, but pin will not
>budge! any suggestions?

There can be a varnish buildup that will prevent the pins from sliding out.  You will need to support the piston somehow and press the pins out.  I used a large C-clamp and some deep sockets.  Be careful not to mar the pistons.

-David


